# stat

## timestamps
(see also man 2 stat)

file timestamp fields inside file metadata:

Access	-	read file
Modify	-	modification file content
Change	-	change file meta data (e.g. permissions)


# important notices:

## mount
if fs is mounted with --noatime then atime is not updated by the filesystem

## touch
-a			changes only the access time
-m			changes only the modification time
-t	STAMP	use [[CC]YY]MMDDhhmm[.ss] instead of current time
-d	STRING	parse string as current time
			mostly free format human readable date string
			can be absolute or relative time
			see also man info

